FBIS4-15860 "drsov070_s_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-070 Daily Report 12 Apr 1994 Georgia Shevardnadze: Air Strikes `Serious Warning' Shevardnadze: Air Strikes `Serious Warning' LD1204130394 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1133 GMT 12 Apr 94 LD1204130394 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Russian BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Albert Kochetkov] [Text] Tbilisi, 12 Apr--Eduard Shevardnadze told the Georgian Information Agency today that NATO air strikes against Serb positions in Bosnia, "especially when backed by the undertakings and peacemaking efforts of the international community, are a serious warning to militant nationalism and separatism." He said, however, that it was necessary "to observe the tradition of holding political consultations in such cases, especially when it concerns UN Security Council member states.
